OVERVIEW :
The Task Management System is a simple Java-based application designed to manage tasks efficiently. 
It allows users to add, update, view, and delete tasks, helping in organizing and prioritizing their work. 
This project is an excellent starting point for understanding object-oriented programming in Java and working with basic Java concepts like classes, objects, and lists.

FEATURES :
Add Task: Create a new task with a title and description.
Update Task: Modify the details of an existing task.
Delete Task: Remove a task from the system.
View Tasks: Display all tasks with their details.
Mark as Complete: Mark a task as completed.

TECHNOLOGIES USED :
Java: Core programming language used to build the application.
IntelliJ IDEA: Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for writing and running the code.
Git: Version control system to manage code changes.
